<span class="displaytext"><h3>(candidate last) supports many of (candidate last)'s initiatives to provide quality affordable health care for all americans</h3><p>washington, d.c.-- new mexico governor and (PARTY NAME) presidential candidate (candidate full) today welcomed (candidate full)'s release of a proposal that virtually mirrors the (candidate last) plan to provide universal health coverage for all americans.</p><p>"health care affects the people of this country more directly than any other issue in this campaign, and i am pleased that senator (candidate last) finally has joined the debate," governor (candidate last) said. "i also am proud to see that she supports most of the initiatives i have outlined in my comprehensive proposal, which is the most effective and responsible way to make sure that every american has the best possible coverage." </p><p>several major components of the (candidate last) proposal announced today-- an individual mandate to obtain coverage, tax incentives to help individuals pay for coverage, and building on the federal employee health plan to provide coverage to all americans-- were announced by (candidate full) on august 7th in council bluffs, iowa. (candidate last) stressed the importance of increasing choices, including the choice to keep your current coverage, instead of bureaucracy, another central element that the (candidate last) campaign picked up on. as if to stress the similarities in the plans, the (candidate last) campaign entitled its plan "the american health choices plan," resembling governor (candidate last)'s "american choices" plan released at the beginning of august.</p><p>governor (candidate last) also expressed his approval of the inclusion of preventive services in (candidate last)'s plan, but stated that his plan would go even further. </p><p>"my plan would require that all health plans in the country cover proven preventive services," governor (candidate last) said. "some insurance companies might fight this requirement, but i believe that no one should go without necessary cancer screenings or other lifesaving preventive care, irrespective of the plan he or she chooses." </p><p>please find the (candidate last) health care plan <a href="http://action.(candidate last)forpresident.com/page/m/a5owgsk5gq7/jhwloz" title="http://www.(candidate last)forpresident.com/issues/healthcare?id=0001">here.</a></p></span>



